  "prompt": "How do I answer a question on Quora?",
  "response": "Answering a question on Quora is straightforward. Here's a step-by-step guide:\n\n1. **Log In**: Ensure you are logged into your Quora account. If you don't have an account, create one.\n\n2. **Find a Question**: Browse questions in topics you are knowledgeable about or search for specific queries.\n\n3. **Select the Question**: Click on the question you want to answer to open it.\n\n4. **Answer the Question**: There should be an \"Answer\" button below the question. Click this button.\n\n5. **Write Your Answer**: A text box will appear. Write your answer in this box. Make sure to provide a clear, concise, and informative response. Include relevant details, examples, or experiences to support your answer.\n\n6. **Formatting and Adding Media**: You can format your text using the tools provided (bold, italics, bullet points, etc.), and you can also add images, links, and videos if relevant.\n\n7. **Review**: Proofread your answer to correct any errors and ensure it effectively addresses the question.\n\n8. **Submit**: Once you\u2019re satisfied with your answer, click the \"Submit\" button.\n\nOptional tips:\n- **Engagement**: Engage with comments on your answer to provide further clarification if needed.\n- **Follow Topics**: Follow topics that interest you to see more questions in your feed.\n- **Upvotes and Feedback**: Pay attention to feedback and upvotes on your answers to improve your responses in the future.\n\nFollowing these steps should help you successfully contribute to discussions on Quora!",
